ces. We\u2019ll guide you through choosing the best option for your home based on size, fuel type, energy efficiency, and your budget. We install a variety of water heater types, including gas, electric, and tankless water heaters.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you\u2019ve selected the type of heater and specific model, we\u2019ll provide you with an estimate that details labor, the unit, and other associated costs. Installation usually takes a few hours depending on the type of system and any necessary modifications. With a final inspection, we\u2019ll ensure your installation complies with local building codes and safety standards and walk you through how to operate and maintain your new water heater.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Water heater maintenance<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Regular maintenance benefits the efficiency, reliability, and lifespan of your water heater, reducing lifetime costs on premature repairs and replacements. We perform a complete inspection that covers all your water heater\u2019s components, such as valves and heating elements, to ensure it\u2019s working as it should. Other maintenance tasks include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Flushing out sediment and mineral buildup<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Calibrating and adjusting the thermostat<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Inspecting the anode rod<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>For more information or to schedule an appointment for water heater repair in Carrollton, contact us today at&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:4698874874\"><strong>(469) 887-4874<\/strong><\/a>.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Types of Water Heaters We Service<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>At Medley, we service different types of water heaters to accommodate the needs of each household. Each system type has its own advantages, and the right choice for you depends on your home\u2019s hot water demand, layout, and other factors. Our plumbing team repairs, installs, and services these types of water heaters:&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Conventional water heaters:\u00a0<\/strong>Typically fueled by gas or electricity, these water heaters\u00a0heat and store hot water in a tank until it\u2019s needed.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tankless water heaters:\u00a0<\/strong>These energy-efficient models heat water on demand without a storage tank.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Heat pump water heaters:\u00a0<\/strong>These systems use heat pump technology to heat your water, pulling hot water from the surrounding air and transferring it to heat water in a storage tank.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Solar water heaters:\u00a0<\/strong>Solar heaters transform sunlight into solar energy to heat the water in your home.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Addressing Your Water Heater Concerns<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Whatever your concern, Medley\u2019s plumbing team is here to help. Our water heater technicians are just a call away, ready to diagnose and address all your water heater issues promptly and efficiently. If it isn\u2019t repairable, we\u2019ll guide you through the water heater replacement process.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Call our team if you notice these signs that your water heater needs repair or replacement:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Leaks:\u00a0<\/strong>Leaky water heaters are a common homeowner problem. Leaks result from damaged tanks, corroded pipes, or faulty valves and can lead to water damage if left unaddressed.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>No hot water:\u00a0<\/strong>Cold water that should be warm is a clear sign of water heater problems. Various issues cause no hot water, sometimes as simple as a tripped breaker or more complex component malfunctions.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Low hot water pressure:\u00a0<\/strong>Sediment buildup, failing valves, and other issues lead to low hot water pressure.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Water heater noises:\u00a0<\/strong>Popping, banging, or other sounds may indicate sediment buildup or faulty components.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Unpleasant water heater smells:\u00a0<\/strong>Bacteria in your tank or worn anode rods may create sulfur smells, similar to rotten eggs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Pilot light problems:\u00a0<\/strong>Poor venting, condensation, gas supply problems, and numerous other issues may cause your gas water heater\u2019s pilot light to go out, preventing your unit from heating.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>High energy bills:\u00a0<\/strong>Strangely high energy bills may stem from your water heater working inefficiently due to an underlying problem.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Discolored water:\u00a0<\/strong>Rust-hued water indicates sediment or corrosion in the tank, which sometimes forewarns tank deterioration and failure.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Aging system:\u00a0<\/strong>If your water heater is over 15 years old and experiencing frequent or costly malfunctions, replacement is often the most cost-effective solution.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Call Medley for Water Heater Services in Carrollton<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Rely on Medley water heater services to get the most from your system. Our commitment to your satisfaction means we don\u2019t consider our job done until your water heater operates with optimal efficiency and reliability \u2014&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/www.callmedley.com\/contact-us\/#book\">contact us<\/a>&nbsp;or book a service online.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Frequently Asked Questions<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h5 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>How often should I schedule water heater maintenance?<\/strong><\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p>Schedule professional water heater maintenance once per year to keep sediment buildup and wear in check.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h5 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>How much will my water heater repair cost?<\/strong><\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p>Repair costs vary depending mainly on the type of fix and the components involved.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Water Heater Services